To give [credit to Jim Garrison][1], [`Number`][2] is not [`Comparable`][3] so a [`Comparator`][4] needs to be defined for the Number data type. This can be done as such.

    static Comparator&lt;Number&gt; NumberComparator = new Comparator&lt;Number&gt;(){

        public int compare(Number n1, Number n2) {

            BigDecimal N1,N2;
            N1 = new BigDecimal(String.valueOf(n1));
            N2 = new BigDecimal(String.valueOf(n2));
            return N1.compareTo(N2);

        } 
    };
